OL,3,CUkraine enters fifth year of war with
OL,4,Ccivilians increasingly baring the brunt
OL,6,FFor Europe, it has been a strategic
OL,7,Fawakening, shattering assumptions that
OL,8,Fa large-scale land war on the
OL,9,Fcontinent was a relic of the past.
OL,11,FIf nothing else, this war has forced a
OL,12,Frecalibration of defence alliances and
OL,13,Fsecurity priorities.
OL,15,FAnd of course, the spectre of
OL,16,FPresident Trump has taken away any
OL,17,Fsense of security and certainty.
OL,19,FThe central question now is not simply
OL,20,Fwho holds which territory, but who can
OL,21,Fsustain resolve.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
